    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Romero</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 291.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 30th ultimo, proposing, by instruction of your Government, the
                    conclusion of a new convention, extending for the period of one year from
                    December 24, 1897, the provisions of the convention of March 1, 1889, in order
                    that the International Water Boundary Commission may be enabled to conclude the
                    examination and decision of the cases before it.</p>
                <p>I favor the proposition, and inclose herewith a draft of a convention in the
                    English language. If it prove acceptable to you and you will furnish me with the
                    Spanish text, I shall be pleased to have the convention prepared in the two
                    languages for signature.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
